President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Howard A. Husock as a member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting. Husock is currently Vice President for Policy Research at the Manhattan Institute and also directs the Institute's Social Entrepreneurship and Philanthropy Initiative. He has a background in public policy and management, having served as Director of Case Studies at the John F. Kennedy School of Government at Harvard University. He has also worked as a producer, director, and reporter at WGBH Boston, receiving three Emmy Awards and the Robert F. Kennedy Journalism Award. Husock has been a Contributing Editor to City Journal since 1998 and holds a B.S. in Journalism from Boston University.